The paper deals with algorithms for computing edit distance, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in various fields such as natural language processing, bioinformatics, and data mining. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve dynamic programming, approximation algorithms, and data structures. These topics are typically studied in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG).
